  </div>
  <div class="faq-content">
  <%= link_to root_path, class: "faq-back-btn" do %>
  <%= image_tag "back_button.png", alt: "Back", class: "faq-back-btn-img" %>
<% end %>

  <%= image_tag "https://cdn.hackclub.com/019d2b47-bc84-7e30-b668-8798a1980081/rules_title-9f12a43a.png", alt: "Rules", class: "faq-title" %>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2 class="faq-section-heading">— General Rules</h2>
    <p class="faq-a">If the following rules are not respected, your project may receive hour reductions or be rejected by our team, so please read carefully:</p>
    <ul class="faq-list">
      <li>Once you purchase the grant from the shop, you must wait for your <a href="https://hcb.hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="faq-link">HCB</a> grant card to be issued. Refunds are not possible, so do not purchase anything out of pocket (unless explicitly requested by a staff member) before receiving the grant.</li>
      <li>As with every YSWS program, the project must be properly tracked using <a href="https://hackatime.hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="faq-link">Hackatime</a> or <a href="#tracking-system" class="faq-link">journaling</a>. Any activity logged before the official start of the event will not be counted.</li>
      <li>No fraud*, no double-dipping with other Hack Club programs, and no excessive use of AI.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2 class="faq-section-heading">— Ship Requirements</h2>
    <ul class="faq-list">
      <li><a href="https://github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="faq-link">Github</a> opensource page with frequent commits (every 30min - 1h)</li>
      <li><a href="#tracking-system" class="faq-link">Tracking system</a> mandatory</li>
      <li>Live Demo working</li>
      <li>A final proof (screenshot / short video / whatever) to show the improvement</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section" id="tracking-system">
    <h2 class="faq-section-heading">— Info</h2>
    <p class="faq-a"><strong>Tracking System:</strong></p>
    <ul class="faq-list">
      <li><strong>Software</strong> → Track time with <a href="https://hackatime.hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="faq-link">Hackatime</a> (if you have problems setting it up, ask for help in the <a href="https://hackclub.enterprise.slack.com/archives/C0AEQ8ZJ7EU" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="faq-link">Slack channel</a>)</li>
      <li><strong>Hardware</strong> → Track time with <a href="#tracking-system" class="faq-link">journaling system</a></li>
      <li><strong>Art</strong> → Track time with any method you prefer.<br>NOTE: You can work on art for up to 10% of your total hours (e.g., out of 75 project hours, only 7.5 can be labeled as art).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="faq-a" style="margin-top: 1.25rem;"><strong>*Fraud Meaning:</strong></p>
    <p class="faq-a">Don't cheat the time tracking system. No bots, no fake key presses, no UI manipulation. If you do, you'll be banned from <a href="https://hackatime.hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="faq-link">Hackatime</a> and other participating YSWS / events / programs.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section faq-section--cta">
    <a href="https://hackclub.enterprise.slack.com/archives/C0AEQ8ZJ7EU" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="faq-cta-card-link">
      <%= image_tag "Card_1.png", alt: "Ask a question in #jackpot-help", class: "faq-cta-card" %>
    </a>
  </section>
  </div>
</div>

